main event: Cpl Reginald D. Swenney and other airmen observed a strange light at Kelly AFB, Texas on July 24, 1951.
interesting points: The object moved at an estimated speed of 600-700 mph, The object was observed through binoculars and appeared round, The light varied in color from bright white to orange, The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes, Cpl Swenney noted that the object's maneuvers were beyond the capabilities of known aircraft.
sighted object: a round luminous mass of light
witness description: Military personnel from Kelly AFB including Cpl Reginald D. Swenney and Cpl Leon W. Lenz
